    "narrative": "LawDog\u2019s lineup for April 28th is headlined by **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez**, who commands an elite score of 75.90, benefiting from a favorable matchup against a starter with a 4.59 xERA and a solid lineup placement in the three-hole. He is joined in the \"Strong\" category by **Bryson Stott** (71.93), whose score is buoyed by a significant 15% SP skill advantage and a 13% platoon boost, and **Gleyber Torres** (67.52). **Gleyber Torres** remains a core play today, leveraging a strong BvP history (25 PA) and a platoon advantage against P\u00e9rez to maximize his offensive floor. Meanwhile, **Jonathan Aranda** (64.56) and **Will Smith** (64.01) provide excellent secondary value in the heart of the order, both benefiting from high-tier xWOBA projections and advantageous SP matchups.\n\nWhile the lineup is deep, **Masyn Winn** remains a marginal play at 42.92, hampered by the combination of a tough 3.61 xERA matchup and the restrictive impact of an opposing catcher with an elite 1.89s pop time, which limits his stolen base ceiling. **Matt Chapman** stands out as our most difficult bench decision, missing the starting cut with a 44.35 score. While his base projection is solid, the matchup against Luzardo (3.40 xERA) and the subsequent SP skill penalty ultimately pushed him behind our higher-efficiency starts. We are also monitoring **Tyler Freeman** closely; while his 44.80 score earned him a spot, his matchup against the 2.76 xERA of Burns presents the highest risk of a sub-par performance in today\u2019s slate. We will keep **Luis Arraez**, **Jung Hoo Lee**, and **Drew Gilbert** in reserve to maintain our game cap flexibility, as they fell short of the 40-point efficiency floor required for a start today.",
